# Lab 15 - Secure Shell (SSH)

## 🎯 Objective

The objective of this lab is to configure Secure Shell (SSH) on a Cisco router and securely access the router from a PC using encrypted remote login.

---

## 🛠️ Devices Used

- 1 Cisco 1941 Router
- 1 Cisco 2960 Switch
- 1 PC

---

## 🌐 Network Topology

```
      R1
       |
      SW1
       |
      PC1
```

---

## 📋 IP Addressing

| Device | Interface | IP Address | Subnet Mask |
|---------|-----------|------------|-------------|
| R1 | G0/0 | 192.168.1.1 | 255.255.255.0 |
| PC1 | NIC | 192.168.1.10 | 255.255.255.0 |

**Default Gateway:** `192.168.1.1`

---

## ⚙️ Configuration Summary

### Configure Router Interface

```bash
interface GigabitEthernet0/0
ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
no shutdown
```

---

### Configure SSH

```bash
hostname R1

ip domain-name lab.local

username admin secret Cisco123

crypto key generate rsa
```

Choose:

```text
1024
```

Continue with:

```bash
ip ssh version 2

line vty 0 4
login local
transport input ssh
```

Save the configuration:

```bash
end

write
```

---

## ✅ Verification

Verify SSH status:

```bash
show ip ssh
```

Verify configuration:

```bash
show running-config
```

Connect from the PC:

```bash
ssh -l admin 192.168.1.1
```

