## 📚 Key Learning Outcomes

- Configured SSH on a Cisco router.
- Generated RSA keys for encrypted communication.
- Created a local user for authentication.
- Enabled SSH Version 2.
- Configured VTY lines to allow only SSH access.
- Verified secure remote login from a client PC.

---

## ✅ Result

Successfully configured and verified Secure Shell (SSH) on a Cisco router. Remote access was established securely from the PC using SSH authentication, demonstrating encrypted remote device management.

